techmeme.title: Cisco reports Q3 revenue up 11% YoY to $14.15B, vs. $14.08B est., forecasts Q4 revenue above estimates, and announces CFO Scott Herren will retire on July 26 (Jordan Novet/CNBC)
CoreWeave reports Q1 revenue up 420% YoY to $981.6M, vs. $853M est., and net loss of $314.6M, up from $129.2M a year earlier; CRWV jumps 9%+ after hours (Jordan Novet/CNBC)
Foxconn receives approval from India's cabinet to build a new $435M semiconductor plant, expected to open in 2027, in a joint venture with IT giant HCL Group (Jagmeet Singh/TechCrunch)
Epic has submitted a new version of Fortnite to the US App Store, saying it needs to release a weekly update, after pulling the version it submitted on Friday (Juli Clover/MacRumors)
Grok replied with information about South Africa's "white genocide" when X users asked it to fact-check unrelated topics; the issue appears to have been fixed (Jay Peters/The Verge)
